James F. Major Jr.Chief Financial Officer, Principal Accounting Officer, Executive Vice President and Treasurer, BMC Stock Holdings, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 1 different industries.45$739,365As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. James F. Major, Jr., also known as Jim, serves as Chief Financial Officer, Executive Vice President and Treasurer at BMC Stock Holdings, Inc. and has been its Principal Accounting Officer since March 15, 2017. Mr. Major is responsible for finance and credit activities of BMC Stock Holdings. He served as the Chief Financial Officer, Principal Accounting Officer and Treasurer at Stock Building Supply Holdings, Inc., and its Executive Vice President since 2005. He has ... substantial expertise in financial planning, analysis and reporting, tax planning and compliance. Mr. Major is experienced in multiple types of transactions, including acquisitions and real estate. Mr. Major joined Stock in 1998 as Assistant Controller. Prior to that, he served as an Audit Manager with PricewaterhouseCoopers. He is a Certified Public Accountant and has attended Management Programs at the University of Virginia's Darden School of Business and the International Institute for Management Development in Lausanne, Switzerland. Mr. Major holds a Bachelor of Science in Accounting degree from Wake Forest University in 1993.Read Full Background




